dcterms:creator: L. C. Blum
J.-L. Reymond
dcterms:description: The QM7 dataset is a subset of the GDB-13 database, containing about 1 billion organic molecules with up to seven heavy atoms. It includes 7,160 molecules and their corresponding atomization energies.
dcterms:title: QM7

dcterms:creator: L. Ruddigkeit
R. Van Deursen
L. C. Blum
J.-L. Reymond
dcterms:description: The QM8 dataset is a subset of the GDB-17 database, containing four excited-state properties of 21,786 molecules with up to eight heavy atoms, collected using methods including time-dependent DFTs.
dcterms:title: QM8

dcterms:creator: L. Ruddigkeit
R. Van Deursen
L. C. Blum
J.-L. Reymond
dcterms:description: The QM9 dataset provides twelve properties, including geometric, energetic, electronic, and thermodynamic properties, for a subset of the GDB-17 database, consisting of 133,865 molecules with up to nine heavy atoms.
dcterms:title: QM9

dcterms:creator: J. S. Delaney
dcterms:description: The ESOL dataset comprises water solubility data for 1,128 molecules, providing a basis for estimating aqueous solubility directly from molecular structure.
dcterms:title: ESOL

dcterms:creator: D. L. Mobley
J. P. Guthrie
dcterms:description: The FreeSolv dataset consists of experimental and calculated hydration-free energy of 642 small molecules in water, providing valuable data for understanding solvation processes.
dcterms:title: FreeSolv

dcterms:creator: M. Davies
M. Nowotka
G. Papadatos
N. Dedman
A. Gaulton
F. Atkinson
L. Bellis
J. P. Overington
dcterms:description: The Lipophilicity dataset provides experimental results of the octanol/water distribution coefficient for 4,200 molecules, which is an important feature for drug design.
dcterms:title: Lipophilicity
